refentry.refsect1:
&ref.title.attributes;
Attributes for PhpDocumentorTask
&taskAttributes.table.titlesLine.all;
title
String
Title for browser window / package index.
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
destdir
String
Destination directory for output files.
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.yes;
target
String
Alias of destdir ("target" is config param used by PhpDocumentor)
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
output
String
Output format (such as HTML:Smarty:PHP).
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.yes;
sourcecode
Boolean
Generate syntax-highlighted sourcecode file for each file parsed?
false
&attributes.required.no;
examplesdir
String
Path to directory in which to look for example documentation.
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
parseprivate
Boolean
Parse @internal and elements marked private.
false
&attributes.required.no;
javadocdesc
Boolean
JavaDoc-compliant description parsing. Use on/off, default off (more flexibility)
false
&attributes.required.no;
quiet
Boolean
Suppress output to STDOUT.
false
&attributes.required.no;
packageoutput
String
Output documentation only for selected packages. Use a comma-delimited list
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
ignoretags
String
Comma-separated list of tags to ignore (@package, @subpackage, @access and @ignore may not be ignored).
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
defaultpackagename
String
name to use for the default package. If not specified, uses 'default'
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
defaultcategoryname
String
name to use for the default category. If not specified, uses 'default'
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
pear
Boolean
Treat parse dirs as PEAR repository? (package is directory, _members are @access private)
false
&attributes.required.no;
templatebase
String
Set base dirctory of all templates for this parse.
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
undocumentedelements
Boolean
Control whether or not warnings will be shown for undocumented elements. Useful for identifying classes and methods that haven't yet been documented.
false
&attributes.required.no;
customtags
Boolean
Custom tags, will be recognized and put in tags[] instead of unknowntags[].
false
&attributes.required.no;
ignore
String
List of files to ignore, separated by ','.
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;

&ref.title.supportedNestedTags;
<fileset> - Files that should be included for parsing
<projdocfileset> - Files that should be treated as README/INSTALL/CHANGELOG files
